## Selection Algorithm

Given a task, follow this decision tree:

```
1. Extract keywords from task description
2. Match keywords to agent categories:
   - "component", "page", "UI", "form", "layout", "responsive" → frontend-developer
   - "API", "endpoint", "server", "route", "middleware" → backend-architect
   - "database", "schema", "migration", "query", "index" → database-optimizer
   - "auth", "login", "signup", "session", "JWT", "OAuth" → backend-architect
   - "deploy", "CI/CD", "Docker", "infrastructure", "hosting" → devops-automator
   - "test", "spec", "coverage", "assertion" → evidence-collector
   - "security", "vulnerability", "audit", "XSS", "CSRF" → security-architect
   - "design", "mockup", "wireframe", "prototype" → ui-designer
   - "performance", "speed", "latency", "benchmark" → performance-benchmarker
   - "accessibility", "WCAG", "a11y", "screen reader" → accessibility-auditor
   - "SEO", "meta tags", "sitemap", "robots.txt" → seo-specialist
   - "legal", "privacy", "GDPR", "compliance", "terms" → legal-compliance-checker
   - "docs", "README", "documentation", "API docs" → engineering-technical-writer
3. If multiple categories match, pick the most specific agent
4. If no clear match, default to @senior-developer
5. Return: { agent, confidence, reasoning }
```

## Output Format

When asked to select an agent:

```json
{
  "task": "Build the user profile page with avatar upload",
  "selected_agent": "@frontend-developer",
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "UI component with file upload — core frontend work",
  "backup_agent": "@senior-developer",
  "specialist_support": ["@ui-designer for visual polish if needed"]
}
```
